    • deduplicate

      public void deduplicate()
      Reduces tree size by merging duplicate nodes, if possible. This reduces the resources required by the tree without affecting behaviour. Calling this method may take a significant amount of time for large trees. Deduplication is therefore generally performed only once, during dictionary construction and just prior to writing the final version of the dictionary to a file.

      This method will note affect the number of nodes returned from getNodeCount(), which returns the number of effective nodes (merged nodes are counted each time they occur). However, it will result in reduced memory use and smaller file size on write. Typical large dictionaries will be 20-40% of their original size after deduplication.
